Paula Duncan https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Paula_Duncan 0 Paula Margaret Duncan (born 15 September 1952) is an Australian actress. Her numerous television roles include playing Nurse Lisa Brooks in The Young Doctors (1976–77), Detective Danni Francis in Cop Shop (1977–83), for which she twice won the Logie Award for Most Popular Actress, Lorelei Wilkinson in Prisoner (1986), Janet Bryant in Richmond Hill (1988) and Bridget Jackson in Home and Away (1990). Her sister is actress Carmen Duncan. Paula_Margaret_Duncan ( born 15_September_1952 ) is an_Australian_actress .
